If I understood your question correctly, you want to use `appendRow` at the top of the Spreadsheet. If so, there is a workaround for it. First you will need to insert a row at the top of the document, and after that you will be able to put values there. An example code would be:

    sheet.insertRowBefore(1);
    sheet.getRange(1, 1, 1, 4).setValues([&quot;A&quot;, &quot;B&quot;, &quot;C&quot;, &quot;D&quot;]);

Doing it will *push* all the existing rows to the bottom while you append a new row at the top. You can learn more about `insertRowBefore` in [its documentation][1]. I hope that this fulfills your question, but don&#39;t hesitate to tell me if I mistook your issue, so I can help you better.


  [1]: https://developers.google.com/apps-script/reference/spreadsheet/sheet#insertrowbeforebeforeposition

